# Highschool LMS Implementation Plan

## Objective
Deliver the following additions across teacher, student, and shared portal experiences:
1. Teacher `My Classes` student operations (details + subject-grade access).
2. Register-marking workflow for register-class teachers (attendance + timetable ownership).
3. Gradebook-category linking during assignment/quiz creation.
4. Portal-specific Help page with function-level help icons and user-manual content.

## Current Sprint Scope
- Implement now: item `1` and item `3`.
- Plan only (defer build): item `2` and item `4`.

## Item 1: Teacher My Classes Operations
### Functional Requirements
- Add operating actions on teacher `My Classes` roster rows:
  - `Eye` action: open learner details (exclude login PIN).
  - `Grades` action: open learner grades for the selected subject class.
- Keep class and student list behavior unchanged for existing navigation.

### UI/UX Plan
- Update `src/pages/dashboard/teacher/ClassManagement.tsx`:
  - Replace generic row action button with explicit icon actions.
  - Add `Student Details` dialog with profile, registration, and assignment info only (no PIN).
  - Add `Student Subject Grades` dialog for subject classes.
  - Disable grade action for register/home classes (subject-grade view is subject-class scoped).

### Data Plan
- Reuse existing context data:
  - `useRegistrationData` for class rosters.
  - `useAssignments` and `useSubjects` for assignment/quiz results.
- Fetch subject-gradebook setup and scores from:
  - `assignment_groups`
  - `student_gradebook_scores`

### Acceptance Criteria
- Teacher can click eye icon on any learner row and view non-sensitive details.
- Teacher can click grades icon (subject class) and see linked assessment performance.
- PIN is not rendered anywhere in teacher learner details modal.

## Item 2: Register Marking Function (Planned)
### Functional Requirements
- Teachers assigned as class teacher to a register class can:
  - Mark daily attendance (present/absent/late/etc).
  - Manage register timetable responsibilities.
  - Track class attendance history by date and learner.

### Proposed Implementation
- Add teacher route/page: `Register & Timetable`.
- New data model (or confirm existing):
  - `register_attendance_sessions` (register_class_id, date, teacher_id, status)
  - `register_attendance_entries` (session_id, student_id, mark, note)
  - `register_timetable_slots` (register_class_id, day, period, activity, owner)
- Add principal oversight/report hooks later.

### Dependencies / Risks
- Requires schema + RLS updates for attendance tables.
- Requires timezone-aware date handling for daily session boundaries.

## Item 3: Gradebook Setup Score Linking for Assignments/Quizzes
### Functional Requirements
- When creating/editing assignment or quiz, teacher can choose a gradebook setup category
  (e.g. `Quizzes & Assignments`, `Tests & Exams`, `Extra Curricular Activities`).
- Selected category must persist as `groupId` so student assessment records show category placement correctly.

### UI/UX Plan
- Assignment editor (`AssignmentManagement.tsx`):
  - Load subject `assignment_groups`.
  - Add `Gradebook Category` selector in Assessment Settings.
  - Persist selected category on create and edit.
- Quiz editor (`CreateQuiz.tsx`):
  - Load subject `assignment_groups`.
  - Add category selector in quiz settings panel.
  - Persist category for draft and publish flows.

### Data Plan
- Reuse existing schema/fields:
  - `assignments.group_id`
  - `quizzes.group_id`
  - `assignment_groups` for per-subject category definitions

### Acceptance Criteria
- Teacher can select any configured gradebook category during assignment/quiz setup.
- Created/updated assignment or quiz stores selected `group_id`.
- Student grade views place those records under the selected category column.

## Item 4: Help Page + Contextual Help Icons (Planned)
### Functional Requirements
- Add Help page entry in side nav for each portal (student/teacher/principal).
- Help page contains portal-tailored user manual sections.
- Add per-page/per-function help icons linked to relevant manual section snippets.

### Proposed Implementation
- Add route/page per role:
  - `student/help`, `teacher/help`, `principal/help`
- Store manual content as structured config:
  - role -> page -> function -> help text
- Reusable `HelpIcon` component with tooltip/popover + deep-link to Help page section.

### Dependencies / Risks
- Requires agreement on final manual content copy and section hierarchy.

## Rollout Order
1. Ship item 1 UI + data wiring.
2. Ship item 3 category selection + persistence.
3. QA pass: teacher flows + student grade visibility checks.
4. Begin item 2 schema and feature build.
5. Begin item 4 documentation and contextual help layer.

## Validation Plan
- Manual teacher QA:
  - open `My Classes` -> class -> learner row actions.
  - verify learner details exclude PIN.
  - verify grades modal renders subject-linked data.
- Manual assessment QA:
  - create assignment + quiz with chosen gradebook category.
  - verify category appears in student grade records under correct setup column.
- Regression:
  - existing assignment/quiz creation and editing remain functional.
  - existing class list navigation remains functional.
